    "description": {
      "gm": "",
      "value": "<p>Your companion is a boar or pig.</p>\n<p><strong>Size</strong> Small</p>\n<p><strong>Melee</strong> <span class=\"pf2-icon\">1</span> tusk, <strong>Damage</strong> 1d8 piercing</p>\n<p><strong>Str</strong> +3, <strong>Dex</strong> +1, <strong>Con</strong> +2, <strong>Int</strong> -4, <strong>Wis</strong> +2, <strong>Cha</strong> +0</p>\n<p><strong>Hit Points</strong> 8</p>\n<p><strong>Skill</strong> Survival</p>\n<p><strong>Senses</strong> low-light vision, scent (imprecise) 30 feet</p>\n<p><strong>Speed</strong> 35 feet</p>\n<p><strong>Support Benefit</strong> Your boar gores your foes. Until the start of your next turn, your Strikes that damage a creature in your boar's reach also deal [[/r 1d6[persistent,bleed]]] damage. If your boar is nimble or savage, the persistent bleed damage increases to [[/r 2d6]]{2d6}.</p>\n<p><strong>Advanced Maneuver</strong> @Compendium[pf2e-animal-companions.AC-Advanced-Maneuvers.EwCqdvU8WOw2SSxm]{Boar Charge}</p>"
